"n.眩晕 【英】 n.眩晕(a dizzy，confused state of mind) 【考】 hemorrhage : bleeding / vertigo : dizziness(程度: 大出血→流血/眩晕→ 头昏) 【记】 verti(转)+go(走)→ 转着走→眩晕 【例】 Looking out of the window still gives him vertigo.(从窗户往外 望仍会使他眩晕) n. 眩晕(混乱、迷失方向的状态) 【记】verti转, go走－转着走－眩晕 【参】vertiginous(adj 旋转眩晕的) 【类】hemorrhage: bleeding = vertigo: dizziness大出血是过分流血 = 眩晕是过分头昏vertigo: nauseate = ? 眩晕使作呕 = ? 【记】vert 转 + go 转着走→晕；vertical go 垂直着走，乘电梯也会晕 【相关】advert 广告，使转移注意力而留意, avert转移，convert转变,divert转向，evert外转，extrovert性格外向，introvert内向，interconvert 互转，invert向里转，pervert向破，坏的方向转→反常，revert回转→回复；subvert从底下转→推翻 vertigo (n.)  early 15c., from Latin vertigo ""dizziness, sensation of whirling,"" originally ""a whirling or spinning movement,"" from vertere ""to turn"" (see versus)."
